{"schemaVersion":1,"bookId":"situational-15000","unitId":"scene-311","title":"礼仪禁忌","sectionId":"chapter-14","sectionTitle":"人文历史需了解","pageStart":1515,"pageEnd":1520,"extractionMethod":"text-layer","wordEntryCount":22,"duplicateEntryCount":26,"pages":[{"number":1515,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"311 礼仪禁忌"},{"type":"section","text":"Step1 场景词"},{"type":"entry","text":"cultural etiquette文化礼仪","headword":"cultural etiquette"},{"type":"entry","text":"a breach of protocol违反礼仪的行为","headword":"a breach of protocol"},{"type":"entry","text":"convention [kənˈvenʃn]","headword":"convention"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.（某种情况下的）习俗，惯例"},{"type":"note","text":"◎stick to convention墨守成规"},{"type":"entry","text":"gentleman [ˈdʒentlmən]","headword":"gentleman"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.绅士"}]},{"number":1516,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"gentlewoman [ˈdʒentlwʊmən]","headword":"gentlewoman"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.淑女，贵妇人"},{"type":"entry","text":"upper class 上层社会","headword":"upper class"},{"type":"entry","text":"middle class 中产阶级","headword":"middle class"},{"type":"entry","text":"upper middle class 上中产阶级","headword":"upper middle class"},{"type":"entry","text":"kiss [kɪs]","headword":"kiss"},{"type":"definition","text":"n./v.亲吻"},{"type":"note","text":"◎goodbye kiss吻别"},{"type":"entry","text":"nutation [njuːˈteɪʃn]","headword":"nutation"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.点头"},{"type":"entry","text":"shake up摇匀","headword":"shake up"}]},{"number":1517,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"restrain from抑制；制止","headword":"restrain from"},{"type":"entry","text":"restrained [rɪˈstreɪnd]","headword":"restrained"},{"type":"definition","text":"a.矜持的，内敛的"},{"type":"entry","text":"behave oneself well 举止得体","headword":"behave oneself well"}]},{"number":1518,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"decent [ˈdiːsnt]","headword":"decent"},{"type":"definition","text":"a.正派的；规矩的；得体的"},{"type":"entry","text":"funeral taboo丧葬禁忌/holiday taboo节日禁忌","headword":"funeral taboo"},{"type":"entry","text":"stranger [ˈstreɪndʒə(r)]","headword":"stranger"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.陌生人"},{"type":"note","text":"◎stranger anxiety陌生人焦虑"}]},{"number":1519,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"prohibition [ˌprəʊɪˈbɪʃn]","headword":"prohibition"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.禁止"},{"type":"note","text":"◎food prohibition饮食禁忌"},{"type":"entry","text":"personal privacy 私人隐私","headword":"personal privacy"},{"type":"entry","text":"gossiper [ˈɡɒsɪpə(r)]","headword":"gossiper"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.搬弄是非者，爱嚼舌根的人"},{"type":"entry","text":"rumour [ˈruːmə(r)]","headword":"rumour"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.谣言"},{"type":"note","text":"◎rumour monger造谣者"}]},{"number":1520,"blocks":[{"type":"section","text":"Step2 学以致用"},{"type":"entry","text":"Personal space个人空间","headword":"Personal space"},{"type":"text","text":"Personal space varies as you travel the globe. In Mediterranean"},{"type":"text","text":"countries, if you refrain from touching someone's arm when talking to them"},{"type":"text","text":"or if you don't greet them with kisses or a warm embrace, you'll be"},{"type":"text","text":"considered cold. In Thailand, the head is considered sacred — never even"},{"type":"text","text":"pat a child on the head."},{"type":"text","text":"环游世界的时候你会发现各地的个人空间概念各不相同。在地中"},{"type":"text","text":"海的一些国家，如果你和人们交谈时避免碰到他们的手臂，或见面问"},{"type":"text","text":"候时没和他们亲吻或者热情拥抱，他们会认为你很冷淡。在泰国，人"},{"type":"text","text":"们认为头很神圣——不要拍别人的头，即使是小孩。"}]}]}